  keyworded ~arch for ppc, bug 267052

*wicd-1.6.0_alpha2 (25 Apr 2009)

  25 Apr 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  +wicd-1.6.0_alpha2.ebuild:
  Version bump to new alpha release for more testing. Highlights include a new
  CLI interface and improved backend handling

  26 Feb 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org>
  -files/wicd-1.5.2-docs.patch, -wicd-1.5.2.ebuild, -wicd-1.5.4.ebuild,
  -wicd-1.5.6.ebuild, -wicd-1.5.7-r1.ebuild, -wicd-1.5.8.ebuild:
  remove old ebuilds affected by CVE-2009-0489

  25 Feb 2009; Tobias Scherbaum <dertobi123@gentoo.org>
  wicd-1.5.9-r1.ebuild:
  ppc stable, bug #258596

  15 Feb 2009; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> wicd-1.5.9-r1.ebuild:
  amd64/x86 stable, bug #258596

*wicd-1.5.9-r1 (12 Feb 2009)

  12 Feb 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> -wicd-1.5.9.ebuild,
  +wicd-1.5.9-r1.ebuild:
  revert back to our init script, bug 238278

  12 Feb 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> wicd-1.5.9.ebuild:
  init script isn't executable by default, sorry - didn't catch that

  09 Feb 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> wicd-1.5.9.ebuild:
  rely on upstream's init script, they package everyone elses and are
  receptive to changes. Remove init script after <=1.5.8 leaves the tree

*wicd-1.5.9 (06 Feb 2009)

  06 Feb 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> +wicd-1.5.9.ebuild:
  1.5.9
   * Fixed security hole in DBus configuration file
   * Fixed the TTLS template
   * Added support for Crux to the setup.py

  09 Jan 2009; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org> wicd-1.5.7-r1.ebuild,
  wicd-1.5.8.ebuild:
  Added the ~ppc keyword for bug #250515.

*wicd-1.5.8 (06 Jan 2009)

  06 Jan 2009; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> +wicd-1.5.8.ebuild:
  Version bump:
  1.5.8
   * Improved pm-utils support
   * Improved UTF-8 support

  26 Dec 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> wicd-1.5.7-r1.ebuild:
  Drop pm-utils dep down to >=pm-utils-1.1.1, bug #252306

*wicd-1.5.7-r1 (26 Dec 2008)

  26 Dec 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> -wicd-1.5.7.ebuild,
  +wicd-1.5.7-r1.ebuild:
  Add rdepend on pm-utils and drop ~ppc keyword because they don't have
  pm-utils yet. If you don't use pm-utils-1.2.3, you will end up with problems
  like bug 252306

*wicd-1.5.7 (22 Dec 2008)

  22 Dec 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> +wicd-1.5.7.ebuild:
  Version bump:
  1.5.7
   * Improved suspend/resume support
   * Encryption details containing % signs now work
   * Many other bug fixes

